{"id": 6488, "title": "Ticket #6488: SlotMergeConstraint failures ignored", "description": "<blockquote>\nDue to a typo in <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4398\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4398'); return false;\" title=\"STARTD_CRON should have a way to set slot specific values\">#4398</a></span>, a <code>SlotMergeConstraint</code> which fails is ignored, meaning that an otherwise-unconfigured startd cron job which writes an ad with a <code>SlotMergeConstraint</code> will actually update all slots.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2017-Dec-12 11:17:36 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nWhere \"fail\" means \"does not evaluate to a value convertible to boolean\", particularly including \"undefined.\"\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Dec-12 11:19:36 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>Code Review</strong>\n\n<p>TJ points out that since we always return from this conditional, we also need to always set <code>pattr_used</code>.\n\n</p><p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Dec-12 15:48:04 by johnkn:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE_REVIEW</strong> changes look good.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Dec-12 11:32</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/7169199d3f39fa719788980cb22d1236bc90c03d\">[52978]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6488\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6488'); return false;\" title=\"SlotMergeConstraint failures ignored\">#6488</a></span>) Always set the pattr_used, since it's definitive if it exists.  (By Todd L Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\